# MODE: AGENT — E2E ONLY AUTO-FIX LOOP (REAL INTEGRATION)

## GOAL
Run ONLY customer-web E2E: targeted → validation → stability (10/10) → release-gate.
If any fails, fix minimal root cause and rerun until all green — WITH REAL INTEGRATION.

## HARD RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
- No product features.
- No mocks in validation/release-gate. Always enforce: VITE_E2E_MOCK="false".
- UI prefs disable flag is E2E-scoped only (never global defaults).
- DB bootstrap policy: Prisma first → verify tables → SQL fallback; CI hard-fail if both fail.
- NO TEST BYPASS:
  - Never use page.goto('about:blank') in E2E.
  - Never comment out API validation.
  - Never replace assertions with placeholders.

## REQUIRED HEALTH CHECKS (FAIL FAST)
Before running Playwright (use the ports printed by release-gate logs):
- Backend must respond 200: http://localhost:<BACKEND_PORT>/api/health
- Frontend must respond 200/HTML: http://localhost:<FRONTEND_PORT>/

If either fails → exit 1 (do not run Playwright).

## RUN ORDER
1) pnpm --filter customer-web test:e2e:targeted
2) pnpm --filter customer-web test:e2e:validation
3) pnpm --filter customer-web test:e2e:stability   (must be 10/10)
4) Release-Gate Proof (PowerShell):
   $env:PRISMA_USER_CONSENT_FOR_DANGEROUS_AI_ACTION="I explicitly consent to the database reset operation for E2E testing"
   $env:VITE_E2E_MOCK="false"
   node scripts/release-gate.mjs --yes
   echo RELEASE_GATE_EXIT_CODE=$LASTEXITCODE

## FIX LOOP BEHAVIOR
If any step fails:
- Identify FIRST failing test and root cause.
- Apply minimal patch (no bypass).
- Rerun the same step until PASS.
- Continue to next step.
- Update docs/e2e/acceptance.md with:
  - timestamp
  - branch/commit
  - summary lines for targeted/validation/stability/release-gate
  - evidence: Real API via Vite proxy, backend port, frontend port, paginated {data,pagination}

## OUTPUT FORMAT
- Summary (targeted/validation/stability/release-gate)
- First failing test + log snippet
- Patch (files + diff)
- Rerun proof (PASS)
- acceptance.md updated